<br>
When the mage has kept his FR under 100, the Fire pets resist the AE about 90% of the time. That 10% where it doesn't happen might just kill you, or it might not.<br>
<br>
With today's gear and spells, 1 or 2 more traditional groups can just take out Rak without the dificulties involved in properly implementing the fire-pet trick.<br>
<br>
The last time I did it was for my shaman. The Fire pets all decided not to resist the same AE.... it was bad. All pets down in under 20 seconds. Mages down shortly after that, along with my shaman and a druid. Rak was only down 10% at that point.<br>
<br>
The Cleric (61), Rogue(61), and Paladin(60) who there for support/clearing took him down another 70% before being wiped out.<br>
